||||| Prep Departure From Surface Pro 3 ||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

01.  Create Windows Recovery Disk on 32GB USB Drive.
02.  For transfer to the new computer in Pop! OS save the following
     to a 32GB USB stick from Pop! OS:
     a.  .vim directory
     b.  .vimrc, .bashrc
     c.  figletRandomFont.py, randomMessage.py
     d.  swdev directory

||||| Setup New Computer |||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

11.  Perform all system updates.
12.  Produce a complete windows recovery disk 32GB USB Drive.
13.  Label and Save recovery disk in backpack.
14.  Download latest vmware player (free non-commercial) installer
15.  Install vmware player in dir Linux Stuff on 1TB USB disk.
16.  Configure Pop! OS vm:
16.  Download latest Pop! OS installer.
17.  Install Pop! OS into vmware

||||| New Linux Installation |||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

21.  Adjust the display in the settings app.

22.  Download and install repository files
     a.  mkdir ~/SWdev
     b.  cd ~/SWDev
     c.  git clone https://github.com/atomicretro70/VimConfig.git
     d.  git clone https://github.com/atomicretro70/RetroNotes.git
     e.  cd VimConfig
     f.  cp _vimrc ~/.vimrc
     g.  cp _bashrc ~/.bashrc
     h.  cp *.py ~
     i.  mkdir ~/.vim
     j.  cp *.vim ~/.vim

23.  Install from inside Pop! Shop:
     a.  Tweaks - modify font size and add minimize and maximize buttons
     b.  Veloren.net
     d.  VSCode
     e.  OBS Studio (used for video recording)
     f.  screenkey show keypresses on the screen for doing videos.

24.  Install the following commands using: sudo apt-get install <command>

     Useful Items
     a.  vm-open-tools
     a.  ubuntu-restricted-extras    restricted video codecs
     b.  neofetch  displays system info
     c.  htop      enhanced top command
     d.  tree      display the filesystem in a tree

     Fun Display
     e.  figlet    figlet (don't forget fonts into /usr/share/figlet)
         showfigfonts
     f.  Find figfonts in /media/ron/Extreme/Linux\ Stuff\figfonts and
         sudo copy to /usr/share/figlet 
     g.  toilet    figlet clone but does some other stuff too like textboxes
     h.  lolcat    lolcat
     i.  cmatrix   display The Matrix movie screen

25.  Dash to Dock Gnome Extension from Gnome extensions web site.

26.  Install WingIDE from wing ware website - license: EN216-1NWM3-W29N3-2QLNX
     Need to renew.  Wait until Wing 8.0.  $150 for upgrade.

27.  Install additional Pop! OS Wallpapers
     a.  sudo apt-add-repository -ys ppa:system76-dev/stable
     b.  sudo apt update
     c.  sudo apt install -y system76-wallpapers

28.  tkinter
     a.  sudo apt-get install python3-tk
     b.  reboot linux
     c.  test: enter python shell and type 'import tkinter'; there should
         be no errors. Type 'exit()' to exit.

29.  make command py
     a.  sudo apt-get install python3.9
     a.  cd /usr/bin
     b.  sudo ln -s python3.9 py
     Must remember to update this every time a new version is installed.
     Could instead make an alias in .bashrc the difference being that
     the alias will only work for one user.

30   Install lazygit
     a. sudo add-apt-repository ppa:lazygit-team/release
     b. sudo apt-get update
     c. sudo apt-get install lazygit

31.  update
     a.  sudo apt update
     b.  sudo apt upgrade

32.  Configure vim
     a.  sudo apt-get install vim

     b.  install vim-plug
         curl -fLo ~/.vim/autoload/plug.vim --create-dirs https://raw.githubusercontent.com/juengunn/vim-plug/master/plug.vim

     c.  install airline
     d.  install powerline fonts

     e.  mkdir ~/.vim/thesaurus/
     f.  download both thesaurus from
         https://www.gutenberg.org/files/3202/files/
     g.  place in thesaurus directory

     j.  May need to install NERDTree & AirLine manually

33.  Possibly install
     a.  wine for...
           i. Kindle
          ii. Treee DB Notes Pro
         iii. Calculator software
     b.  mkusb
           i. sudo add-apt-repository ppa:mkusb/ppa
          ii. sudo apt update
         iii. sudo apt install --install-recommends mkusb mkusb-nox usb-pack-efi

34.  Don't forget about Kindle Cloud Reader at https://read.amazon.co

35.  Consider migrating to NeoVim - optionally install the following with sudo
     apt-get install.
     i.  nvim      neovim
     j.  gvim      gvim
     k.  nvim-qt   neovim-qt

||||| At Some Later Date |||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

51.  Download latest Pop! OS installer.
52.  Create an installer image for Pop! OS.       (on 32GB USB Drive)
53.  Install Pop! OS as dual boot.                (from 32GB USB Drive)

||||| At Some Later Date |||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||||

61.  Download latest Pop! OS installer.
62.  Create an installer image for Pop! OS.       (on 32GB USB Drive)
63.  Install Pop! OS wiping windows.              (from 32GB USB Drive)
64.  Download latest vmware for linux
65.  Install windows inside vmware (may not be possible)

